sec.p:
The voltage equation of the SRM motor is given below,
\begin{align*}
& V_{m}=R_{s} i_{s}+\frac{d \varphi}{d t} \tag{1}\\
& \varphi\left(\theta, i_{s}\right)=L\left(\theta, i_{s}\right) i_{s}(t) \tag{2}
\end{align*}

Putting the value of $\varphi$ we get,
\begin{align*}
& V_{m}=R_{s} i_{s}+L\left(\theta, i_{s}\right) \frac{d i_{s}}{d t}+i_{s} \frac{d L\left(\theta, i_{s}\right)}{d t} \tag{3}\\
& \frac{d L\left(\theta, i_{s}\right)}{d t}=\frac{\partial L\left(\theta, i_{s}\right)}{\partial \theta} \frac{d \theta}{d t}+\frac{\partial L\left(\theta, i_{s}\right)}{\partial i_{s}} \frac{d i_{s}}{d t} \tag{4}
\end{align*}

The voltage equation becomes,
\begin{equation*}
\begin{array}{cl}
& V_{m}=R_{s} i_{s}+l\left(\theta, i_{s}\right) \frac{d i_{s}}{d t}+e_{b}
\forall & l\left(\theta, i_{s}\right)=L\left(\theta, i_{s}\right)+i_{s} \frac{d L\left(\theta, i_{s}\right)}{d t}
& e_{b}=i_{s} \frac{\partial L\left(\theta, i_{s}\right)}{\partial \theta}=\text { back EMF }
\end{array} \tag{5}
\end{equation*}

The torque equation for the SRM drive is given by:
\begin{equation*}
T_{e}=\frac{1}{2} i_{s}^{2} \frac{d L\left(\theta, i_{s}\right)}{d t} \tag{6}
\end{equation*}

The observer equations for the sliding surface and the estimation of flux and then rotor position are listed below:
\begin{align*}
\frac{d \hat{\lambda}}{d t}=-\left(R L^{-1}(\theta, i) \hat{\lambda}\right)+V+K_{\lambda} e_{i} \tag{7}\\
\frac{d \hat{\omega}}{d t}=T_{L}-\frac{1}{J}\left[\frac{1}{2} \hat{\lambda}^{T} \frac{d\left(L^{-1}(\theta, i)\right)}{d \theta} \hat{\lambda}+D \omega\right]+K_{\omega} e_{i} \tag{8}\\
\frac{d \hat{\theta}}{d t}=\hat{\omega}+K_{\theta} e_{i} \tag{9}\\
i=L^{-1}(\theta, i) \lambda \tag{10}\\
e_{i}=\hat{i}-i \tag{11}
\end{align*}

This is used for interfacing the PV with the DC link capacitor at the point of common coupling with the power electronic converter and battery interfaced through the bidirectional DC-DC converter. The output voltage or the voltage at the PCC is evaluated as,
\begin{equation*}
\mathrm{V}_{P C C}=\mathrm{V}_{D C}=\mathrm{G}_{\text {boost }} \times \mathrm{V}_{\text {in }} \tag(12)
\end{equation*}

$\mathrm{G}_{\text {boost }}$ = Boost converter gain = voltage amplification
\begin{equation*}
G_{\text {boost }}=\frac{1}{1-d} \tag(13)
\end{equation*}
Where d represents duty ratio.
